Stellar Locus Regression
FW High


It's best to go to the Wiki for the latest install instructions:

http://code.google.com/p/stellar-locus-regression/w/list


============
QUICK INTALL
============

to install, you need these idl libraries:

idlutils: http://www.astro.princeton.edu/~schlegel/code.html
markwardt: http://www.physics.wisc.edu/~craigm/idl/

and the Schlegel et al. SFD data: http://astro.berkeley.edu/~marc/dust/data/data.html
(high resolution E(B-V) maps only, NGP and SGP), put in some location, $DUST_DIR/maps (not $DUST_DIR/map!!!!)
and put the SFD idl code somewhere and add to IDL_PATH:

in your cshrc or bashrc file (example is bash):


#####

export DUST_DIR=/Users/stalder/stellar-locus-regression/
export SLR_DATA=/Users/stalder/Documents/pisco/stellar-locus-regression/example_data/
export SLR_WORK=/Users/stalder/Documents/pisco/stellar-locus-regression/
IDL_PATH=$IDL_PATH:+/usr/local/idllibraries/idlutils/pro:+/usr/local/idllibraries/cmtotal:+/usr/local/idllibraries/SFD_stuff:+/Users/stalder/stellar-locus-regression/pro

export IDL_PATH

#####

also add in your idl_startup.pro:

usersym,cos(2*!pi*findgen(21)/20.), sin(2*!pi*findgen(21)/20.), /fill ; set psym=8 to be a circle

#####

to check that everything is working:

IDL> slr_demo

